    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#ferri1923"/>, n. <citedRange>15</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.343</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>032700</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Zeus"><name nymRef="#Ζεύς"><expan><abbr>Ζη</abbr><ex>νός</ex></expan></name></persName>,
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" cert="low"><name nymRef="#Εὐεργέτας">Εὐερ<supplied reason="lost">γ</supplied>έ<supplied reason="lost">τα</supplied></name></persName>	 
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> de Zeus, appartenant à Euergetas.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of Zeus, belonging to Euergetas.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> di Zeus, appartenente a Euergetas.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Ferri (<bibl><ptr target="#ferri1923"/>, p. <citedRange>14</citedRange></bibl>) wondered whether <foreign xml:lang="grc">Εὐεργε</foreign> was the beginning of a divine epithet or of a personal name. However, in this area 
                    Zeus is only called <foreign xml:lang="grc">Μηλίχιος</foreign>, whereas the personal name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Εὐεργέτας</foreign>, although 
                    not attested in Cyrenaica, is quite plausible and would fit the context better.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
